(p \land q)\lor(\lnot p \land q)
p\lor q
(a\lor b) \land c \equiv (a \land c) \lor (b \land c)
p\lor \lnot p\equiv T
T \equiv \;\text{true}\;\equiv 1
\begin{align}(p\land q)\lor (\lnot p \land q) & \equiv (p\lor \lnot p) \land q\tag{DL} \\ \\ & \equiv T \land q \tag{LEM}\\ \\  & \equiv q\end{align}
q
(p\land q )\lor (\lnot p\land q) = (p \lor \lnot p )\land q = q
